given the bonus in recognition of the success of his two-year revamping plan
to return Citicorp to health.
Citicorp produced full-year 1992 net profits of Dollars 722m, after a loss
of Dollars 457m in 1991.
But Mr Reed was only awarded 90 per cent of his targeted bonus, reflecting
work still to be done at Citicorp.
