<HEADLINE>
FT  20 FEB 93 / International Company News: Rise in interest payments hits
Asahi Breweries
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMIKO TERAZONO
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ASAHI Breweries, Japan's second largest brewer with a 24 per cent market
share, yesterday posted a sharp fall in unconsolidated profits for 1992
partly due to a rise in interest payments on its bonds.
Asahi, which holds a 17 per cent stake in Foster's Brewing of Australia,
reported that pre-tax profits plunged 19.6 per cent to Y14bn (Dollars
115.7m) despite a 4.3 per cent rise in sales to Y770.6bn. After-tax profits
fell 34.2 per cent to Y4bn.
Operating profits surged 90.7 per cent to Y35.9bn thanks to cost cutting and
a sharp increase in bulk sales of non-alcoholic beverages, with a large
profit margin.
For the full year to December, Asahi expects pre-tax profits to rise 3.3 per
cent to Y14.5bn on a 5.1 per cent increase in sales to Y810bn.
</TEXT>
